This paper is about real-time object detection using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes new boosting algorithms to address the asymmetric learning problem, which involves optimizing loss objectives, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of column generation technique, which is a method used in optimization problems, suggesting that it could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM).
